  "text": "## Apache Kafka Consumer Offset Management Architecture\n\nThe consumer offset management in Apache Kafka is implemented across the following key components:\n\n### Core Data Structures\n\n1. **OffsetAndMetadata** - Represents a committed offset with metadata:\n   - Server-side implementation: `group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/OffsetAndMetadata.java` - Stores offset, leader epoch, metadata, commit timestamp, and topic ID\n   - Client-side implementation: `clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/OffsetAndMetadata.java` - Used by consumers to track offsets\n\n### Storage in __consumer_offsets Topic\n\nOffsets are persisted as records in the `__consumer_offsets` internal topic with:\n- **OffsetCommitKey** and **OffsetCommitValue** generated records (from protocol definition)\n- Records contain group ID, topic, partition, offset, metadata, and timestamps\n- **Log compaction** maintains only the latest offset for each group-topic-partition combination\n\n### GroupCoordinator Interface and Implementation\n\nThe offset commit/fetch handler is the `GroupCoordinator` interface (`group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinator.java`) with implementations:\n\n- **GroupCoordinatorService** (`group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinatorService.java`) - High-level coordinator service that delegates to shard\n- **GroupCoordinatorShard** (`group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinatorShard.java`) - Replicated state machine handling offset commit/fetch for a specific partition\n\n#### Offset Commit Handler\nThe commit flow:\n1. **handleOffsetCommitRequest** in `KafkaApis.scala` - Receives OffsetCommitRequest from client\n2. Routes to **GroupCoordinator.handleOffsetCommit** via GroupCoordinatorService\n3. **GroupCoordinatorShard.handleOffsetCommit** - Processes and generates CoordinatorRecords\n4. **OffsetMetadataManager.handleCommitOffsets** - Stores offset in memory and generates write records\n\n#### OffsetFetch Request Processor\nThe fetch flow:\n1. **handleOffsetFetchRequest** in `KafkaApis.scala` - Receives OffsetFetchRequest\n2. Routes to **GroupCoordinator.fetchOffsets** via GroupCoordinatorService\n3. **GroupCoordinatorShard.handleOffsetFetch** - Validates authorization\n4. **OffsetMetadataManager.fetchOffsets** - Retrieves offsets from memory\n\n### OffsetMetadataManager - Core Offset Storage\n\nThe `OffsetMetadataManager` (`group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/OffsetMetadataManager.java`) manages:\n- **offsets** - Timeline HashMap storing group -> topic -> partition -> OffsetAndMetadata\n- **pendingTransactionalOffsets** - Tracks transactional offsets not yet committed\n- **openTransactions** - Tracks groups with ongoing transactions\n\nKey methods:\n- **handleCommitOffsets** - Handles offset commit requests and generates tombstone records for replacements\n- **fetchOffsets** - Retrieves committed offsets for fetch requests\n- **deleteOffsets** - Deletes offsets (OffsetDelete API)\n- **onPartitionsDeleted** - Cleans up offsets when topics are deleted\n- **cleanupExpiredOffsets** - Removes expired offsets\n\n### Offset Expiry and Compaction Logic\n\n**OffsetExpirationCondition** interface (`group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/OffsetExpirationCondition.java`) defines when an offset expires:\n\n**OffsetExpirationConditionImpl** (`group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/OffsetExpirationConditionImpl.java`) implements expiration based on:\n- Base timestamp (commit timestamp for consumer offsets)\n- Configured retention period (offsets.retention.minutes)\n- Current time\n\n**Offset cleanup** in `OffsetMetadataManager.cleanupExpiredOffsets`:\n- Iterates through all offsets for groups not subscribed to topics\n- Checks if offset has expired using OffsetExpirationCondition\n- Appends tombstone records (null values) for expired offsets\n- Tombstone records enable log compaction to remove old entries\n- Records cleanup metric via OFFSET_EXPIRED_SENSOR_NAME\n\n**Log Compaction**: The __consumer_offsets topic uses log compaction (cleanup.policy=compact):\n- Tombstone records (null values) mark deleted offsets\n- Log cleaner removes entries with identical keys and null values\n- Maintains only the latest offset for each group-topic-partition\n\n### Group Metadata Management\n\nThe `GroupMetadataManager` (`group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupMetadataManager.java`) tracks:\n- Group lifecycle and state\n- Which groups have active offsets\n- Group expiration conditions\n\nDifferent group types support different offset expiration:\n- **ClassicGroup** - Expires based on last commit timestamp\n- **ConsumerGroup** - Expires based on last commit timestamp  \n- **StreamsGroup** - Expires based on last commit timestamp\n- **ShareGroup** - Does not support offset expiration\n\n### Request/Response Protocol\n\nThe offset management uses these protocol requests/responses:\n- **OffsetCommitRequest/Response** - Commits offsets for a consumer group\n- **OffsetFetchRequest/Response** - Fetches committed offsets\n- **OffsetDeleteRequest/Response** - Deletes offsets (Admin API)\n\nProtocol definitions automatically generate key/value classes for __consumer_offsets records.\n\n### Configuration\n\n`GroupCoordinatorConfig` defines critical offset settings:\n- offsetsRetentionMs - How long to keep offsets (default 7 days)\n- offsetMetadataMaxSize - Maximum metadata size per offset\n- offsetsTopicPartitions - Number of partitions in __consumer_offsets\n- offsetsTopicReplicationFactor - Replication factor for offset storage\n\nThis architecture ensures durable, scalable offset management with automatic cleanup and compaction of the __consumer_offsets topic."
}

